  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bc1\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0baf \u0baf\u0bcb\u0b9a\u0ba9\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd !",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The main ideas presented by the protestors to the political party leaders!",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Kota \u2013 A new constitution must be drawn up with a referendum before the end of the term of the interim government that will be formed following Ranil's resignation. The currently arrested protesters and political prisoners should be released.",
        "The empty-faced protestors presented their ideas to the political party leaders and members, demanding that a special mechanism be devised to provide justice to the victims of political revenge, murder and disappearances.",
        "An event where empty face protestors presented their ideas was held today at the National Reading Room in Colombo.",
        "President Gotabaya Rajapaksa should resign as the executive president and the cabinet including Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe should resign.",
        "After the resignation of Kota Ranil government, an interim government should be established keeping in mind the economic, social and political objectives along with the people's struggle.",
        "Short and long-term programs should be implemented to provide relief to the people affected by the economic crisis. Waiver of fuel, gas and education, public transport services, micro-credit and agricultural loans, leasing, small business loans or provision of grace period for repayment.",
        "All the political prisoners, including the currently arrested protesters, should be released and justice should be given to the victims of political persecution.",
        "Also, a special mechanism should be prepared to provide justice to the victims in cases of murder and disappearance.",
        "State funds embezzled by the Rajapaksers over the last two decades should be nationalized with proper investigations and the embezzlers should be punished. Assets amassed illegally by politicians should be audited.",
        "The current tax system should be modified to increase direct tax and reduce direct tax. Tax policy should be modified in a favorable manner for the people of the country.",
        "Following Kotaya Rajapaksa's departure from office, a new constitution must be drafted to ensure people's power. The executive presidential system should be completely abolished.",
        "A new constitution should be drafted with a referendum, right to life should be a fundamental right, the right to consummation should be abolished, and a proper mechanism should be established to hold fair elections.",
        "A mechanism should be devised to ensure the right to reinstate politicians who are not accountable to the people. An environment should be created for the participation of the people in the legislation, apart from the representatives of the people. The rights of education and health sectors should be protected.",
        "The Basic Law should be strengthened to ensure equality and to ensure equality of all castes, religion, language, milk and other cultural identities by completely suppressing the pressures of casteism and nationalism.",
        "The basic objectives of the Interim Government are to implement the above, and the Interim Government to be established should complete the drafting of a new constitution within a period of 12 months.",
        "Members of Parliament MA Sumanthran, Manokaneshan, Jeevan Thondan, Ranjith Mathuma Bandara, Dumintha Dissanayake, Chanakyan Rasamanickam, Harsa de Silva, political parties and civil organizations participated in the event."
      ],
